G. Lin
dcterms:description: The 2-D Sphere Function is a continuous optimization problem where the objective is to minimize the function fS((x1, x2)) = x1^2 + x2^2, with the optimal solution at (0, 0).
dcterms:title: 2-D Sphere Function

dcterms:creator: J. He
G. Lin
dcterms:description: The 2-D Rastrigin Function is a continuous optimization problem defined as fR((x1, x2)) = 20 + (x1^2 - 10 cos(2πx1)) + (x2^2 - 10 cos(2πx2)), with the optimal solution at (0, 0).
dcterms:title: 2-D Rastrigin Function
